visual.name: liquidFillGauge
visual.description: The Liquid Fill Gauge custom visual is perfect to use when you want to visualize data that represents liquid levels. For example, if you have an IoT device that monitors your barbeque grill's propane tank level, you could send that data to Power BI and use the Liquid Fill Gauge to see how empty or full it is from anywhere in the world.

textColor.description: The color of the value text when the wave does not overlap it.

waveTextColor.description: The color of the value text when the wave overlaps it.

size.description: The relative height of the text to display in the wave circle. 1 = 50%

textVertPosition.description: The height at which to display the percentage text within the wave circle. 0 = bottom, 1 = top.

valueCountUp.description: If true, the displayed value counts up from 0 to its final value upon loading. If false, the final value is displayed.

displayPercent.description: If true, a % sign is displayed after the value.

calculatePercentage.description: If true, converts a decimal value to a percentage of the Max Value property.

multiplyBy.description: A number that you would like to multiply the data value by. For example, if you data is .89 and you want it to display 89, then you would enter 100 here.

function.description: None, Absolute, Truncate, Round, Ceiling, Floor

circleColor.description: The color of the outer circle.

circleThickness.description: The outer circle thickness as a percentage of its radius.

circleFillGap.description: The size of the gap between the outer circle and wave circle as a percentage of the outer circles radius.

waveColor.description: The color of the fill wave.

waveHeight.description: The wave height as a percentage of the radius of the wave circle.

waveHeightScaling.description: Controls wave size scaling at low and high fill percentages. When true, wave height reaches its maximum at 50% fill, and minimum at 0% and 100% fill. This helps to prevent the wave from making the wave circle from appear totally full or empty when near its minimum or maximum fill.

waveCount.description: The number of full waves per width of the wave circle.

waveRise.description: Controls if the wave should rise from 0 to its full height, or start at its full height.

waveRiseTime.description: The amount of time in milliseconds for the wave to rise from 0 to its final height.

waveAnimate.description: Controls if the wave scrolls or is static.

waveAnimateTime.description: The amount of time in milliseconds for a full wave to enter the wave circle.

waveOffset.description: The amount to initially offset the wave. 0 = no offset. 1 = offset of one full wave.
